<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<chapter xml:id="ch-more-differentiation" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Differentiation in Several Variables</title>

<introduction>
<p>
  Learning goals:
  <ul>
    <li>
      Calculate the partial derivatives of a function of two variables.
    </li>
    <li>
      Calculate the partial derivatives of a function of more than two variables.
    </li>
    <li>
      Determine the higher-order derivatives of a function of two variables.
    </li>
    <li>
      Determine the equation of a plane tangent to a given surface at a point.
    </li>
    <li>
      Use the tangent plane to approximate a function of two variables at a point.
    </li>
    <li>
      Explain when a function of two variables is differentiable.
    </li>
    <li>
      State the chain rule for two or more independent variables.
    </li>
    <li>
      Determine the directional derivative in a given direction for a function of two variables.
    </li>
    <li>
      Determine the gradient vector of a given scalar-valued function.
    </li>
    <li>
      Explain the significance of the gradient vector with regard to direction of change along a surface or graph.
    </li>
    <li>
      Calculate directional derivatives and gradients in three or more dimensions.
    </li>
  </ul>
</p>  
</introduction>

